The paper proposes a new visualization technique for version-controlled documents, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on collaborative revision process and authoring patterns suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The use of computer code and online discussion boards also suggests cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions large scale computer code and papers authored by a team of scientists, which could be relevant to cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
